article.headline: E. Kentucky 94, Tenn.-Martin 57
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Adam Leonard scored 18 points to lead Eastern Kentucky to a 94-57 win over Tennessee-Martin on Monday night. Leonard led six players in double figures as the Colonels (11-9, 6-6 Ohio Valley Conference) snapped a three-game losing streak in their highest scoring game of the season. Gerald Robinson led Tennessee-Martin (6-18, 4-10) with 14 points. Joseph Bailey added 12 and McKale Jones 11. Mike Rose scored 17 points for Eastern, Julian Mascoll added 14, Josh Taylor had 12, Michael Brock 11 and Jamaal Douglas 10. Leonard made four of his team's 11 3-pointers and scored 12 points in the second half. The Colonels made 14 of their first 17 field goals and shot 71.4 percent (20-28) from the field in the first half. Eastern was 6-of-11 from 3-point range during the half. The Colonels forced 25 turnovers and collected 19 steals. Eastern trailed 11-10 with 12 minutes remaining in the first half but outscored the Skyhawks 25-3 during the next seven minutes to go ahead 35-14. Martin managed just three field goals and three free throws during the final 12 minutes of the half and trailed 48-22 at halftime.
